      1          /**
      2           *  @file
      3           *
      4           *  @brief  Module used to discover the accelerometer that is in the product.
      5           *          Discovery is based on the WHO_AM_I register (or similar register).
      6           *          The module cycles through a list of devices, given a register to read and expected device ID.
      7           *          If the device ID matches the expected value, the module execution is complete.
      8           *          If the device ID does not match the expected value, the module attempts to read the next device ID in the list.
      9           *            **NOTE** If no known device ID is read, this module will continue in a loop until it finds a known device ID.
     10           *
     11           *  @details
     12               @startuml{AccelDiscover_sm.png}
     13                  title AccelDiscover State-Machine
     14                  ' Suppress transition checks
     15          
     16                  [*] --> INTERFACE_MODE
     17          
     18                  INTERFACE_MODE: entry / StartTimer() \n \t SetInterfaceMode()
     19                  INTERFACE_MODE : do / WaitForTimer
     20                  INTERFACE_MODE -->  BOOT_MODE_LOW : evTimerExpired
     21          
     22                  BOOT_MODE_LOW : entry / StartTimer() \n \t SetBootModeLow()
     23                  BOOT_MODE_LOW : do / WaitForTimer
     24                  BOOT_MODE_LOW -->  BOOT_MODE_HIGH : evTimerExpired
     25          
     26                  BOOT_MODE_HIGH : entry / StartTimer() \n \t SetBootModeHigh()
     27                  BOOT_MODE_HIGH : do / WaitForTimer
     28                  BOOT_MODE_HIGH -->  BOOT_DELAY : evTimerExpired
     29          
     30                  BOOT_DELAY : entry / AccelHwInit()
     31                  BOOT_DELAY : do / WaitForBootComplete()
     32                  BOOT_DELAY --> IDENTIFY : evBootComplete
     33          
     34                  IDENTIFY : entry / StartTimer()\n\t AccelReadIdentity()
     35                  IDENTIFY : do / WaitForIdentity()
     36                  IDENTIFY --> BOOT_DELAY : evTimeout
     37                  IDENTIFY --> BOOT_DELAY : evWrongIdentity
     38                  IDENTIFY --> Complete : evIdentityReceived
     39          
     40                  ' The purpose of the COMPLETE state is to have a status to report that the device has been discovered
     41          
     42              @enduml
     43           *
     44           *  @copyright  Copyright 2022. Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     45           */
